Unit-5: Resource and Compute Quota?

IQ) How will you do resource planning in worker nodes?
IQ) How many should be in one cluster and how much cpu and memory required?

	First we need to ask deployment team how much you required for application.

	Example:

	 memory : 256 GB
	 cpu    : 128 cpu

	 256/8 = 32 GB ram required on each worker node.

     Application by-default works on thin concept.
     Thin means kubernetes do not allocate memory and cpu for containers. containers will automatelly allocate respecting to node hardware.

     Types of Quota:
     ===============

     1) Resource/Objective Quota: Pod/deployment/rc/rs/ (rare in use)
     		example:
     			=> Team do not delete objects like deployment once work done.

     2) Compute quota(Cpu/Memory)
      	=> When you need to limit cpu and memory of container.

      	Scope to create quota.
      		A. Deployment scope:
      				a) soft quota (request/reservation)
      				b) hard quota

      			Memory unit
      				1Mi, 1Gi


root@kube-master:~# cat demo.yml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  creationTimestamp: null
  labels:
    app: demo
  name: demo
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: demo
  strategy: {}
  template:
    metadata:
      creationTimestamp: null
      labels:
        app: demo
    spec:
      containers:
      - image: nginx
        name: nginx
        resources:
                requests:
                        memory: 128Mi
                        cpu: 100m            # Guranteed memory(soft quota)
                limits:
                        memory: 200Mi
                        cpu: 100m            # non-granteed memory (hard quota)

root@kube-master:~# kubectl describe  node kube-node2                 <<<== To check node defails

     IQ) What will do if container used 98% memroy?
      	          => increase the replicas so that load will distribute on containers.

    Scaling Types
    1. Vertical : to extend resource like memory, cpu in existing container. (downtime required)
    2. Horijental : To increase the containers count (do not required downtime)

========================================================================================



      		B. Namespace scope

      		Note: you need admin access to set namespace quota

root@kube-master:~# kubectl create ns myns
namespace/myns created
root@kube-master:~# kubectl create quota cka --hard=cpu=800m,memory=800Mi -n myns
resourcequota/cka created

root@kube-master:~# kubectl describe quota cka -n myns
Name:       cka
Namespace:  myns
Resource    Used  Hard
--------    ----  ----
cpu         0     800m
memory      0     800Mi

root@kube-master:~# kubectl edit quota cka -n myns
resourcequota/cka edited
root@kube-master:~# kubectl describe quota cka -n myns
